'''賈克·吕西安·莫諾'''（'''Jacques Lucien Monod'''，{{bd|1910年|2月9日|1976年|5月31日}}）是一位[[法國|法國]][[生物學家|生物學家]]，出生於[[巴黎|巴黎]]，他與[[方斯華·賈克柏|方斯華·賈克柏]]共同發現了[[蛋白質|蛋白質]]在[[轉錄作用|轉錄作用]]中所扮演的調節角色，也就是後來著名的[[乳糖操縱子|乳糖操縱子]]，兩人因此與[[安德列·利沃夫|安德列·利沃夫]]共同獲得了1965年的諾貝爾生理學或醫學獎<ref name="nobelprize2">{{cite web|url= http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1965/index.html|title= The Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine 1965 François Jacob, André Lwoff, Jacques Monod|publisher= Nobelprize.org|accessdate= 30 June 2010|archive-date= 2007-09-12|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070912130759/http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1965/index.html|dead-url= no}}</ref><ref>''The Statue Within: an autobiography'' by [[François_Jacob|François Jacob]], Basic Books, 1988. ISBN 0-465-08223-8 Translated from the French. 1995 paperback: ISBN 0-87969-476-9</ref><ref>''[[Chance_and_Necessity|Chance and Necessity: An Essay on the Natural Philosophy of Modern Biology]]'' by Jacques Monod, New York, Alfred A. Knopf, 1971, ISBN 0-394-46615-2</ref><ref>''Of Microbes and Life'', Jacques Monod, Ernest Bornek, June 1971, Columbia University Press, ISBN 0-231-03431-8</ref><ref>''The Eighth Day of Creation: makers of the revolution in biology'' by Horace Freeland Judson, Simon and Schuster, 1979.  ISBN 0-671-22540-5. Expanded Edition Cold Spring Harbour Laboratory Press, 1996. ISBN 0-87969-478-5. Widely{{quantify|date=February 2016}}-praised{{by whom|date=February 2016}} history of molecular biology recounted through the lives and work of the major figures, including Monod.</ref><ref>''Origins of Molecular Biology: a Tribute to Jacques Monod'' edited by Agnes Ullmann, Washington, ASM Press, 2003, ISBN 1-55581-281-3. Jacques Monod seen by persons who interacted with him as a scientist.</ref>。

此外，他曾預測在基因訊息與蛋白質產物之間，具有[[mRNA|mRNA]]分子作為中介者，此理論後來獲得證實。莫諾同時也是一位[[科學哲學|科學哲學]]作家與音樂家。

